tisfies precision >= 0.5 is unknown until after the critic runs. This conflates a measured result with an experimental condition, making the forbidden case unfalsifiable as a pre-registered threshold: if no arm achieves precision >= 0.5, the case trivially never triggers, yet the claim survives without being tested. The standard requires thresholds 'pre-registered before the first look,' but these thresholds are functions of the very measurements the experiment produces.","counterexample":null}